library(tidyverse)
data(msleep)
msleep

H0: there’s no difference between the mean sleep_total in the sampled population of animal types and the typical value for jabberwockies. HA: the mean sleep_total of the sampled population is significantly higher than the typical value for jabberwokies.

å = 0.05

Average sleep_total is 10.43 hours

msleep %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = sleep_total))+
  geom_histogram(col = "white")

`stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

msleep %>%
  specify(response = sleep_total) %>%
  hypothesise(null = "point", mu = 10.43) %>%
  generate(reps = 10000, type = "bootstrap") %>%
  calculate(stat = "mean")

Response: sleep_total (numeric)
Null Hypothesis: point

null_dist %>%
  get_p_value(obs_stat = obs_stat$mean_sleep_total, direction = "right")

Warning: Please be cautious in reporting a p-value of 0. This result is an approximation based on the number of `reps` chosen in the `generate()` step. See `?get_p_value()` for more information.

Question 3. Perform an appropriate statistical test to determine whether omnivores sleep for significantly longer than herbivores, on average.

H0: omnivore sleep for as long as herbivores on average (μ1 − μ2 = 0) HA: omnivores sleep for significantly longer than herbivores (Ha: μ0 > μ2)

msleep_vore_two %>% 
  specify(sleep_total ~ vore) %>% 
  hypothesize(null = "independence") %>% 
  generate(reps = 1000, type = "permute") %>% 
  calculate(stat = "diff in means", order = c("omni", "herbi"))

Response: sleep_total (numeric)
Explanatory: vore (factor)
Null Hypothesis: independence
msleep_vore_two%>%
  specify(sleep_total ~ vore) %>%
  calculate(stat = "diff in means", order = c("omni", "herbi"))

Response: sleep_total (numeric)
Explanatory: vore (factor)

Question 4. Perform an appropriate statistical test to determine whether the proportion of domesticated animal types in the population of animal types is greater than 5%.

msleep_dom %>%
  specify(response = is_domesticated, success = "TRUE") %>% 
  hypothesize(null = "point", p = 0.05) %>% 
  generate(reps = 10000, type = "draw") %>% 
  calculate(stat = "prop")

Response: is_domesticated (factor)
Null Hypothesis: point
msleep_dom%>%
  specify(response = is_domesticated, success = "TRUE") %>%
  calculate(stat = "prop")

Response: is_domesticated (factor)
